    {
        "content": "<p>Regarding the naming, Iâ€™ve been wondering for a long time whether we should systematically name <code>Foo.factor</code> the map obtained by the universal property of <code>Foo</code>, and <code>Morphism.foo</code> for the functorial morphism coming for it, in the sense that you introduce <code>Foo</code>s on both side in the \"natural\" way. For example, we would have <code>DirectSum.factor</code> for the universal property and <code>LinearMap.directSum</code> for the linear map between direct sums given by linear maps between each factors (I donâ€™t know if thatâ€™s clear, I try to avoid LaTeX on mobileâ€¦)</p>",
        "id": 379400083,
